subjective.hpi: Patient reports a 3-day history of watery diarrhoea (approximately 6 times per day) with no blood. Associated symptoms include intermittent, crampy pain in the Left Lower Quadrant (LLQ) which does not radiate. Patient experienced bilous vomiting with no haematemesis and fever for 1 day, but both have resolved. Patient feels lethargic and weak. History includes eating Chinese takeaway food 4 days ago; wife and children also ate but have no vomiting, diarrhoea, or other symptoms. Condition is affecting Activities of Daily Living (ADLs), requiring patient to stay near the toilet frequently.
subjective.patient_history: Asthma (on inhalers). Non-smoker, non-drinker. Social history: Accountant, lives with wife and children.

plan.patient_instructions: Conservative management: rest and push fluids. Take Paracetamol if fever and OTC Dioralyte for hydration. Review in 3-5 days if not better, or return earlier if symptoms worsen.
